SIMPLE: without
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Without
<hw>With*out"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prep.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>withoute</ets>, <ets>withouten</ets>, AS. <ets>wi⟦edh⟧<?/tan</ets>;
<ets>wi⟦edh⟧</ets> with, against, toward + <ets><?/tan</ets> outside,
fr. <ets><?/t</ets> out. See <er>With</er>, <pos>prep.</pos>,
<er>Out</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>On or at the outside of; out of; not within; <as>as,
<ex>without</ex> doors</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Without</qex> the gate⟦br⟧
Some drive the cars, and some the coursers rein.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Out of the limits of; out of reach of;
beyond.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Eternity, before the world and after, is <qex>without</qex> our
reach.</q> <rj><qau>T. Burnet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not with; otherwise than with; in absence of,
separation from, or destitution of; not with use or employment of;
independently of; exclusively of; with omission; <as>as,
<ex>without</ex> labor; <ex>without</ex> damage</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I wolde it do <qex>withouten</qex> negligence.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wise men will do it <qex>without</qex> a law.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Without</qex> the separation of the two monarchies, the most
advantageous terms . . . must end in our destruction.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is no living with thee nor <qex>without</qex> thee.</q>
<rj><qau>Tatler.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To do without</b></col>. <cd>See under <er>Do</er>.</cd>
-- <col><b>Without day</b></col> <ety>[a translation of L. <ets>sine
die</ets>]</ety>, <cd>without the appointment of a day to appear or
assemble again; finally; as, the Fortieth Congress then adjourned
<xex>without day</xex>.</cd> -- <col><b>Without recourse</b></col>.
<cd>See under <er>Recourse</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Without</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Without
<hw>With*out"</hw>, <pos>conj.</pos> <def>Unless; except; -- introducing
a clause.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You will never live to my age <qex>without</qex> you keep
yourselves in breath with exercise, and in heart with joyfulness.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir P. Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Now rarely used by good writers or speakers.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Without</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Without
<hw>With*out"</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>On or art the
outside; not on the inside; not within; outwardly; externally.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Without</qex> were fightings, within were fears.</q>
<rj><qau>2 Cor. vii. 5.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Outside of the house; out of doors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The people came unto the house <qex>without</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Without-door</ent>⟦br⟧
